1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the development of a soft robotic finger with embedded sensing capabilities for physical interaction with the environment. 
2. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper discusses the design and fabrication of the soft robotic finger, which involves mechanical engineering principles. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a solution for physically safe human-robot interaction, which involves control and system integration aspects. 
4. cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper describes the integration of optical fibers as sensors inside the soft robotic finger, which involves embedded systems design. 
5. cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper mentions the use of moisture-proof materials for the sensor integration, which may involve electromagnetic properties of materials.
